 :tx/rationale "AUDIT F-ERR-001: 1,180 unwrap() calls across both crates — panic surface analysis. PROBLEM: 719 unwrap/expect calls in braid-kernel, 461 in braid CLI. ~90% are in test code. ~35 are in production paths. Most concerning: query/graph.rs:60-61 get_mut(src).unwrap() in add_edge (panics if node not pre-added), seed.rs:3084,3121 kept.pop().unwrap() (panics on empty vec), bilateral.rs:326,408,587 partial_cmp().unwrap() (panics on NaN — see F-TYPE-004). Most production unwraps are provably safe (documented invariants like 'committed transactions always have a tx_id') but ~10 lack safety proof comments. JUSTIFICATION: NEG-INTERFACE-004 requires 'No Error Without Recovery Hint.' An unwrap that panics produces a stack trace, not a recovery hint. For a system claiming lab-grade quality, every production unwrap must either (1) be provably unreachable (with SAFETY comment), or (2) be replaced with proper error propagation. SOLUTION: (1) Add // SAFETY: ... comments to all provably-safe production unwrap() calls. (2) Replace the ~5 genuinely risky unwraps with proper error returns. (3) Enable clippy::unwrap_used for non-test code. VERIFICATION: cargo clippy with unwrap_used lint shows zero violations in non-test code. DEPENDENCIES: Independent. F-TYPE-004 is a subset (NaN-specific unwraps). FILES: All .rs files in crates/. SEVERITY: Medium. WAVE: 1. EFFORT: 4h."
